Alan B. Colberg





 President and CEO 
 Assurant, Inc.  

 
 
Tweet 












Mr. Colberg is President and CEO, Assurant, Inc. In this role, Mr. Colberg works closely with leadership of the business units to align the company’s enterprise-wide strategy with business-level innovation and growth plans.
Mr. Colberg joined Assurant as executive vice president of marketing and Business Development for Assurant in March 2011. Before joining Assurant, Mr. Colberg worked for Bain & Company, Inc. for 22 years, founding and heading Bain’s Atlanta office since 2000. He also served as Bain’s global practice leader for financial services, advising leading global companies including Assurant.
In 2010, Consulting Magazine recognized Mr. Colberg as one of the world's top 25 consultants and for his excellence in the financial services sector. He received a Master of Business Administration from Harvard Business School and is a graduate of the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania, with highest honors.
Mr. Colberg has long been active in civic leadership roles having served as chairman of the board of the Atlanta International School and on the boards of the Woodruff Arts Center and the Metro Atlanta Chamber of Commerce. 
 


 







  


 


