Alan B. Colberg  Chief Executive Officer, President and Director, Assurant, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships55$7,797,881As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Alan B. Colberg has been the President of Assurant, Inc. since September 16, 2014 and has been its Chief Executive Officer since January 1, 2015. Mr. Colberg serves as Chief Executive Officer and President at Assurant Health, Inc. Mr. Colberg served as Executive Vice President of Marketing and Business Development at Assurant, Inc. since March 28, 2011 until September 2014. He joined Assurant following a 22-year career with Bain & Company, Inc., where he founded ...  and for the past 11 years, headed its Atlanta Office. Mr. Colberg served as Managing Director of the Atlanta office and Co-head of North America Financial Services practice at Bain & Co. He focused on the practice areas of strategy, new business development and process innovation. While at Bain, he has helped clients create real change and superior results in a variety of industries, ranging from consumer finance, apparel, professional services, pharmaceuticals, health care, consumer products and steel to beverages, banking, insurance and computers. He was the driving force behind the opening and rapid expansion of Bain's Atlanta office and Southeastern USA services. He served as President and Chief Operating Officer of Commercial Financial Services and as a marketing and financial analyst at Procter and Gamble. He has been an Independent Director of CarMax Inc. since October 21, 2015. He has been a Director of Assurant, Inc. since January 1, 2015. Mr. Colberg has been a Member of Advisory Board at Ingenious Med, Inc. since May 2005. He serves on the Board of Trustees for the Atlanta International School, the Atlanta College of Art and the Metro Atlanta Chamber of Commerce. In 2010, he was recognized by Consulting Magazine as one of the world's top-25 consultants and for his excellence in the Financial Services sector. Mr. Colberg received a Bachelor of Science degree with highest honors in Accounting and Finance from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania. He holds an MBA from Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




